Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated serum creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment, and elevated chloride. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), but no hematuria, nitrites, or leukocytes. These findings may indicate early diabetic nephropathy or other renal dysfunction; urinary tract infection is less likely. Recommend further renal evaluation and correlation with clinical context.
